column12: Videojet ink composition
column13: Ink compositions suitable for ink jet printing on a variety of substrates including metal, synthetic polymers and glass, are provided. The compositions are characterized by excellent weathering properties, are fade-resistant, abrasion-resistant and, when heated to temperatures of about 300.degree. F., exhibit resistance to aircraft hydraulic fluids. The preferred compositions comprise essentially a colorant or combinations thereof, an epoxy-phenolic binder resin component, a solvent mixture containing alcohol, water, methyl ethyl ketone or methyl cellosolve and, optionally, an electrolyte.
column15: FELL DAVID A

column12: ABSORBENT ARTICLE HAVING A MULTILAYER BLENDED CORE AND A METHOD OF FORMING
column13: An absorbent core for use in an absorbent article, the absorbent article and a method of forming the absorbent core and article are disclosed. The absorbent core includes at least three absorbent layers. The first absorbent layer is formed from a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent and has a predetermined basis weight. The two remaining absorbent layers are positioned below the first absorbent layer. Each of the two remaining absorbent layers is formed from a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent and each has a basis weight which is at least equal to the basis weight of the first absorbent layer. The absorbent article includes a liquid permeable bodyside liner and a liquid-impermeable baffle enclosing the above described absorbent core. The method describes forming the absorbent layers into an absorbent core and using the absorbent core to form an absorbent article.
column15: FELL DAVID ARTHUR

column12: Contactless jet printing method, printing ink composition therefor, and articles including containers bearing indicia, printed using said composition.
column13: The ink composition, which permits indicia to be successfully printed on metal or plastics surfaces even in the presence of lubricating or moisture films, comprises a dye, an epoxy resin binder and a solvent blend consisting of water, lower monohydric alcohol(s), low molecular weight glycol ether(s) such as the cellosolves, and aliphatic ketone(s). The alcohol(s) and ketone(s) possess 1 to 3 and 3 to 8 carbon atoms respectively. Ink jet printing using the composition on food or beverage bottles or cans, or on plastics insulated wire, yields indicia which are resistant to fading, abrasion and attack by hot hydraulic fluid.

column12: Videojet ink for printing on food products
column13: Ink compositions suitable for ink jet printing on a variety of substrates and particularly food products, for example citrus fruit, and method of marking such products are provided. The compositions are characterized by their ability to penetrate the waxed surfaces of such foods as citrus fruits to provide markings therein. Preferred compositions comprise essentially a solution of a food dye or combination thereof, a binder resin component, a solvent mixture containing alcohol, water and an organic compound selected from the group consisting of aliphatic hydrocarbons having 5 to 12 carbon atoms and aliphatic ketones; and, optionally, an electrolyte.

column12: UN NUCLEO ABSORBENTE PARA UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE, EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE QUE LO COMPRENDE Y EL METODO PARA FORMAR DICHO NUCLEO Y DICHO ARTICULO ABSORBENTE
column13: Se describen un núcleo absorbente para usar en un artículo absorbente, el artículo absorbente y un método para formar el núcleo absorbente y el artículo. El núcleo absorbente incluye por lo menos tres capas absorbentes. La primera capa absorbente está formada de un material estabilizado que contiene un superabsorbente y que tiene un peso base predeterminado. Las dos capas absorbentes restantes están colocada debajo de la primera capa absorbente. Cada una de las dos capas absorbentes restantes está formada de un material estabilizado que contiene un superabsorbente y cada una tiene un peso base el cual es por lo menos igual al peso base de la primera capa absorbente. El artículo absorbente incluye un revestimiento enfrentado al cuerpo permeable al líquido y un separador impermeable al líquido que encierra el núcleo absorbente descripto anteriormente. El método describe la formación de las capas absorbentes en un núcleo absorbente y el uso del núcleo absorbente para formar un artículo absorbente.
column15: FELL DAVID A

column12: Displaying Interactive Content from a Received Video Stream on a Second Screen
column13: A first user terminal comprises a television receiver receiving a user selected TV channel comprising a main video stream. The first terminal further comprises a first controller and an output for outputting the main video stream of the selected channel to a first screen (6). A second user terminal, e.g. tablet or laptop computer, comprises a second screen (16), a wireless transceiver in connection with the first terminal, and a second controller communicating with the first controller via the wireless connection. The first terminal TV receiver receives metadata (e.g. a server link or time window for access to the interactive content) relating to interactive content associated with the main video stream, and the first controller forwards the metadata to the second terminal via the connection. The second controller processes the metadata and outputs the interactive content to the second screen, such that the interactive content is displaced to the second terminal screen whilst the main video stream continues to be displayed on the first terminal screen. An EPG may also be provided in addition to the TV channel and the metadata.
column15: FELL DAVID;;MIDDLETON SIMON

column12: INTERACTIVE TELEVISION SYSTEM
column13: A method comprising: determining a hierarchical time structure for a received television channel relative to its main video content, the hierarchical time structure comprising a plurality of nested levels in the form of a lowest level and at least one higher level ordered from lower to higher level, each level comprising a plurality of time windows, each time window of the lowest level corresponding to a different respective one of said items of interactive content, and each time window of each of the one or more higher levels corresponding to a different respective plurality of the time windows of its next lower level in the hierarchical time structure; and receiving user operations at a user terminal. A first one of said user operations accesses on screen the item of interactive content associated with a current lowest level time window, and at least a second one of said user operations generates a list of the items of said interactive content corresponding to a plurality of lower level time windows within a current higher level time window.

column12: Processing supplementary interactive content in a television system
column13: Items of interactive content such as advertisements or commercials A1, A2 etc in main video content such as program parts P1a, P1B etc on a television system are handled by: determining a hierarchical time structure having a plurality of nested levels ordered from a lowest L1 to a highest L3 level, the lowest level having a respective time window for each item of interactive content and the level above it having a time window corresponding to a plurality of time windows at the lowest level; and receiving user operations at a user terminal, where a first user operation accesses on screen an item of interactive content associated with a current lowest level time window and a second user operation generates a list of interactive content items falling within a higher level time window embracing the accessed interactive content item. The second user operation may cause the list to be generated on a device e.g. tablet or laptop external to the user terminal on which the main video content is viewed. The first and second user operations may be single and double button presses on a remote control unit.

column12: Urinary incontinence device and a method of making the same
column13: A urinary incontinence device is disclosed along with a method of making the device. The device includes a resilient member and a non-absorbent which at least partially encloses the resilient member. The non-absorbent and the resilient member are formed into an elongated softwind having a first end and a second end. The softwind is folded upon itself such that the first and second ends are aligned adjacent to one another and the softwind contains at least two folds therebetween. The resilient member extends between at least two of the folds. The softwind is then compressed into an elongated pledget having an insertion end and a trailing end with the resilient member located at least in the insertion end. The resilient member is capable of expanding at least a portion of the pledget to provide a supportive backdrop for a woman's urethra when inserted into a woman's vagina. The method includes the steps of enclosing the resilient member by the non-absorbent, folding the two materials to form a softwind, folding the softwind into a generally M-shape configuration and then compressing the softwind into an elongated pledget.
column15: ZUNKER MARYANN;;FELL DAVID ARTHUR

column12: Dispositivo para a incontinência urinária expansìvel em forma de calota e um processo para a sua fabricação
column13: "<DISPOSITIVO PARA A INCONTINêNCIA URINáRIA EXPANSìVEL EM FORMA DE CALOTA E UM PROCESSO PARA A SUA FABRICAçãO>". é descrito um dispositivo para a incontinência urinária expansível em forma de calota juntamente com um processo para a sua fabricação. O dispositivo inclui um elemento resiliente e um não-absorvente que envolva pelo menos parcialmente o elemento resiliente. O não-absorvente e o elemento resiliente são formados em um softwind alongado que tem uma primeira extremidade, uma segunda extremidade, uma primeira porção localizada adjacente à primeira extremidade, uma segunda porção localizada adjacente à segunda extremidade, e uma terceira porção localizada entre a primeira e a segunda porções. O softwind é dobrado sobre si mesmo de modo que a primeira e a segunda extremidades são alinhadas adjacentes uma à outra, formando-se uma alça fechada. A primeira e a segunda porções são então unidas para reduzir a alça fechada e a terceira porção é transformada em um formato de calota. O softwind é em seguida comprimido em um chumaço alongado tendo uma extremidade de inserção e uma extremidade traseira com o elemento resiliente localizado pelo menos na extremidade de inserção. O elemento resiliente é capaz de fazer expandir pelo menos uma porção da terceira porção para proporcionar sustentação para a uretra de uma mulher quando adequadamente inserido na vagina de uma mulher. O processo inclui as etapas de se envolver o elemento resiliente com o não-absorvente, dobrando-se os dois materiais para formar um softwind, dobrando-se o softwind de modo tal que seja formada uma alça fechada e transformando-se a alça fechada de modo a se ter um formato de calota, comprimindo-se em seguida o softwind em um chumaço alongado.

column12: AN EXPANDABLE DOME-SHAPED URINARY INCONTINENCE DEVICE AND A METHOD OF MAKING THE SAME
column13: An expandable dome-shaped urinary incontinence device is disclosed along wit h a method of making the device. The device includes a resilient member and a non-absorbent which at least partially encloses the resilient member. The no n- absorbent and the resilient member are formed into an elongated softwind having a first end, a second end, a first portion located adjacent to the first end, a second portion located adjacent to the second end and a third portion located between the first and second portions. The softwind is folde d upon itself, such that the first and second ends are aligned adjacent to one another and a closed loop is formed. The first and second portions are then brought together to minimize the closed loop and the third portion is transformed into a dome shape. The softwind is then compressed into an elongated pledget having an insertion end and a trailing end with the resilient member located at least in the insertion end. The resilient member is capable of expanding at least a portion of the third portion to provide support for a woman's urethra when properly inserted into a woman's vagina. The method includes the steps of enclosing the resilient member by the non- absorbent, folding the two materials to form a softwind, folding the softwin d such that a closed loop is formedand transforming the closed loop into a dom e shape, and then compressing the softwind into an elongated pledget.

column12: Opaque jet ink compositions
column13: The present invention relates to non-pigmented jet ink compositions and to a method of producing opaque coded messages therewith. The compositions comprise, on a weight basis, between 2 and 15% of a gellable cellulose ester having a hydroxyl content of from 2 to 8%, from 1.5 to 15% of a binding agent selected from the group consisting of alkali soluble rosin type and maleic type resins, polyvinyl acetate resins, and acrylic resins, and a solvent blend, the blend consisting essentially of an organic solvent system and a non-solvent, said non-solvent comprising from 2 to 10% by weight of the ink compositions. Preferred solvents are methanol, acetone, methyl ethyl ketone and ethyl acetate, while the preferred non-solvent is water. Upon evaporation of the solvent blend, the resultant dry films scatter light incident thereto whereby the opaque images are produced. In a particularly preferred embodiment, a hygroscopic salt is included in the composition as an opacity enhancement agent.

column12: Dispositivo para incontinência urinária e processo para fabricação do mesmo
column13: <B>DISPOSITIVO PARA INCONTINêNCIA URINáRIA E PROCESSO PARA FABRICAçãO DO MESMO<D> é revelado um dispositivo para incontinência urinária juntamente com um processo para fabricação do dispositivo. O dispositivo inclui um elemento resiliente e um não-aborvente o qual, pelo menos parcialmente, encobre o elemento resiliente. O não-absorvente e o elemento resiliente são conformados em um enrolamento flexível alongado possuindo primeira e segunda extremidades. O enrolamento flexível é dobrado sobre si próprio, tal que, as primeira e segunda extremidades estão alinhadas adjacentes uma à outra e o enrolamento flexível contém pelo menos duas dobras entre o mesmo. O elemento resiliente estende-se entre pelo menos duas dobras. O enrolamento flexível é então comprimido em uma pequena compressa alongada possuindo uma extremidade de inserção e uma extremidade de fuga com o elemento resiliente localizado pelo menos na extremidade de inserção. O elemento resiliente é capaz de expandir pelo menos uma porção da pequena compressa para prover uma tela de fundo de sustentação para a uretra feminina, quando inserido dentro da vagina da mulher. O processo inclui as etapas de envolver o elemento resiliente pelo não-absorvente, dobrar os dois materiais para formar ume enrolamento flexível, dobrar o enrolamento flexível em uma configuração geralmente em forma de M e então comprimir o enrolamento flexível em uma pequena compressa alongada.

column12: A URINARY INCONTINENCE DEVICE AND A METHOD OF MAKING THE SAME
column13: A urinary incontinence device is disclosed along with a method of making the device. The device includes a resilient member and a non-absorbent which at least partially encloses the resilient member. The non-absorbent and the resilient member are formed into an elongated softwind having a first end and a second end. The softwind is folded upon itself such that the first and second ends are aligned adjacent to one another and the softwind contains at least two folds therebetween. The resilient member extends between at least two of the folds. The softwind is then compressed into an elongated pledget having an insertion end and a trailing end with the resilient member located at least in the insertion end. The resilient member is capable of expanding at least a portion of the pledget to provide a supportive backdrop for a woman's urethra when inserted into a woman's vagina. The method includes the steps of enclosing the resilient member by the non-absorbent, folding the two materials to form a softwind, folding the softwind into a generally M-shape configuration and then compressing the softwind into an elongated pledget.

column12: DISPOSABLE UNDERPANTS AND METHOD OF PROVIDING THE SAME
column13: A three dimensional disposable underpant is disclosed having an absorbent core skewed forward by a factor of no more than 0.10. The absorbent core is positioned within the front, central, and back sections of the disposable underpant such that the length of the absorbent core in the back section of the disposable underpant divided by the length of the absorbent core in the front and central sections of the disposable underpant is less than 0.10, and the length of the absorbent core in the front section of the disposable underpant is greater than the length of the absorbent core in the back section of the disposable underpant. In one aspect, the disposable underpant includes elasticized leg and waist openings, resulting in the underpant being stretchable about the hip and stomach regions of a user.

column12: Dynamic recognition of web addresses in video
column13: One embodiment described herein may take the form of a system or method for dynamically recognizing an Internet address within a video or audio component of a multimedia presentation on a distribution system or network such as, but not limited to, a satellite, cable or Internet network. In general, the embodiment may analyze the audio portion of the presentation or one or more frames of a video component to detect the presence of a web address within the one or more frames. In the embodiment where the audio portion is analyzed, the system may perform a voice recognition or a similar analysis on the audio portion to detect the utterance of a web address. Similarly, one embodiment analyzing the one or more frames of the video component may comprise performing an optical character recognition (OCR) of the frame.

column12: BED PAD
column13: The present invention provides a solution to improving the absorbent structure of a bed pad (20) to prevent leakage by folding the absorbent structure (32) at least twice to form a central channel (38) and a pair of oppositely disposed side dams (40). By creating a central channel (38) and side dams (40), lateral leakage of bodily wastes is reduced and performance of the bed pad (20) is increased. Hence in one aspect, the invention resides in a bed pad (20) including an absorbent structure (32) disposed adjacent a bottomsheet (30), the absorbent structure having a stabilized absorbent material, and the absorbent structure is folded at least twice. The bed pad having a width WP, the absorbent structure having a width WA, and the ratio of WA/WP is from about 0.2 to about 0.8.

column12: System and Method for Providing User Recommendations
column13: The invention generally relates to the field of recommendations of viewable content, and in particular to the recommendation of live and pre-recorded video streams. A system, apparatus and method of providing recommendations of viewable content from a plurality of viewable content to a user substantially in real time, the method comprises: generating viewing data from viewing of said viewable content by one or more other users substantially in real time, said viewing data comprises data such as program details, viewers ratings and opinions and user data associated with each of said other users, said user data comprising at least an identity of said other users; filtering said viewing data by one or both of said viewable content data and said user data; distributing via a network said viewing data to one or more of said users substantially in real time in response to a content characteristic of said filtered viewing data matching a corresponding user characteristic of said one or more users; decoding said viewing data to extract said viewable content data and said user data; processing said extracted viewable content data and said extracted user data to determine one or more statistics of one or both of said extracted viewable content data and said extracted user data; and displaying one or more of said statistics, said viewable content data and said user data to provide a recommendation of viewable content to said user substantially in real time based on viewing data from said one or more other users.
column15: FELL DAVID ARTHUR;;NOBLE ROBERT JOHN

column12: İdrarını tutamayanlar için üriner alet ve yapılması için metod.
column13: Idrar tutamayanlar için üriner aleti ve bu aletin yapilmasina iliskin metod açiklanmaktadir. Emici olmayan madde ve esnek madde uzatilmis ve birinci ve ikinci ucu bulunan yumusak sargi içinde olusturulur. Yumusak sargi, birinci ve ikinci uçlar birbirine bitisecek sekilde ayni hizaya getirilmis ve onlarin arasinda en az iki kat ihtiva edecek sekilde kendi etrafinda katlanmistir. Esnek madde en az iki kat arasinda uzanir. Yumusak sargi daha sonra en azindan yerlestirme kisminda esnek maddenin yer aldigi, yerlestirme ve sevk uçlarina sahip uzatilmis tampon bezinin içine kompres edilir. Bu metod esnek maddenin emici olmayan maddeyle eklenmesi, yumusak sargi olusturmak üzere yumusak sarginin genel M sekli konfigürasyonu seklinde katlanmasi ve sonra yumusak sarginin uzatilmis tampon bezi içine kompres edilmesi asamalarini ihtiva eder.
column15: ZUNKER MARY ANN;;FELL ARTHUR DAVID

column12: MODULATING ENDOGENOUS BETA-ENDORPHIN LEVELS
column13: Systemic beta-endorphin can be elevated in response to cutaneous irradiation, including ultraviolet and ionizing radiation. Increases in systemic beta-endorphin levels associated with cutaneous irradiation can be modulated with opiate receptor antagonists, particularly compounds that antagonize opioid receptor binding by beta endorphin.

column12: Genişleyebilen kubbe şeklinde idrar kaçırma cihazı ve bunu yapma yöntemi.
column13: Genisleyebilen kubbe seklinde bir idrar kaçirma cihazi, bu cihazi yapma yöntemiyle birlikte açiklanir. Cihaz, bir elastik eleman ve elastik elemani en azindan kismen kapatan bir emici olmayan madde içerir. Emici olmayan madde ve elastik eleman, bir birinci uca, bir ikinci uca, birinci uca bitisik bir birinci bölüme, ikinci uca bitisik bir ikinci bölüme ve birinci ve ikinci bölümler arasinda bulunan bir üçüncü bölüme sahip uzatilmis bir yumusak sargi haline getirilir. Yumusak sargi, birinci ve ikinci uçlar birbirleriyle bitisik hizalanacak sekilde kendi üzerinde katlanir ve kapali bir halka olusturulur. Sonra birinci ve ikinci bölümler, kapali halkayi küçültmek için bir araya getirilir.

column12: Absorbent garment with expandable absorbent element
column13: An absorbent garment comprises a chassis and an absorbent element. A method for using the absorbent garment also is provided, together with a method for assembling the absorbent garment.

column12: AN ANGULAR RATE SENSOR
column13: An angular rate sensor or gyro includes a ring-like resonator (1) mounted by support beams (2) extending from the inner periphery of the ring (1) to a bo ss (4) on a base (3). The support beams (2) are flexible and allow the resonato r (1) to vibrate in response to electrostatic drive means (6, 8) in a substantially undamped oscillation mode to permit the resonator to move relative to the support means in response to turning rate. The support beams (2) and resonator (1) are made from crystalline silicon. Electrostatic sensi ng means (7, 9) are provided for sensing movement of the resonator (1). The dri ve means (6, 8) and sensing means (7, 9) have plate-like elements made from crystalline silicon having surfaces located substantially normal to the plan e of the resonator (1) at a spacing from the adjacent outer periphery of the resonator (1). The ratio of the thickness of the resonator (1) at the outer periphery (1b) to the width of the spacing (11) between the periphery (1b) a nd the element surfaces (10) is in the range of from 10:1 to 40:1.
column15: HOPKIN IAN DAVID;;FELL CHRISTOPHER PAUL;;TOWNSEND KEVIN

column12: VERFAHREN ZUM REDUZIEREN DES VORSPANNUNGSFEHLERS IN EINEM VIBRATIONSSTRUKTURSENSOR
column13: Bias error is reduced in a vibrating structure sensor having primary and secondary pick-off means (2, 3, Fig.2) separated by a fixed angular amount (45) with respect to the vibrating structure by summing a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal 10 into the secondary pick-off means output signal 15 or subtracting a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal 10 from the secondary pick-off means output signal 15 effectively to reduce or increase the angular separation of the secondary pick-off means (3) from the primary drive means (1) by an amount sufficient to set the rate output signal from the vibrating structure to zero and thereby minimise bias error.

column12: VIBRATIONSSTRUKTURKREISEL MIT SCHWINGUNGSDÄMPFERSYSTEM
column13: A vibration damper assembly for a ring resonator of a vibrating structure gyroscope has a female portion attachable to a body of the gyroscope so as to have limited resiliency with respect to the body in a direction substantially perpendicular to the body. A male portion is fixedly attachable at one end to a resonator of the gyroscope, projectable into the female portion and fixedly attachable at its other end in and to the female portion. The assembly permits damping of vibratory movement of the resonator in a direction substantially perpendicular thereto whilst retaining stiffness and freedom to vibrate for the resonator in the plane thereof.

column12: Sensor for vinkelhastighet
column13: An angular rate sensor or gyro includes a ring-like resonator (1) mounted by support beams (2) extending from the inner periphery of the ring (1) to a boss (4) on a base (3). The support beams (2) are flexible and allow the resonator (1) to vibrate in response to an electrostatic drive (6, 8) in a substantially undamped oscillation mode to permit the resonator to move relative to the support in response to turning rate. The support beams (2) and resonator (1) are made from crystalline silicon. Electrostatic sensors (7, 9) are provided for sensing movement of the resonator (1). The drive (6, 8) and sensors (7, 9) have plate-like elements made from crystalline silicon having surfaces located substantially normal to the plane of the resonator (1) at a spacing from the adjacent outer periphery of the resonator (1). The ratio of the thickness of the resonator (1) at the outer periphery (1b) to the width of the spacing (11) between the periphery (1b) and the element surfaces (10) is in the range of from 10:1 to 40:1.
column15: FELL CHRISTOPHER PAUL;;TOWNSEND KEVIN;;HOPKIN IAN DAVID

column12: PROCESS FOR REDUCING BIAS ERROR IN A VIBRATING STRUCTURE SENSOR
column13: Bias error is reduced in a vibrating structure sensor having primary and secondary pick-off means (2, 3, Fig.2) separated by a fixed angular amount (45) with respect to the vibrating structure by summing a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal 10 into the secondary pick-off means output signal 15 or subtracting a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal 10 from the secondary pick-off means output signal 15 effectively to reduce or increase the angular separation of the secondary pick-off means (3) from the primary drive means (1) by an amount sufficient to set the rate output signal from the vibrating structure to zero and thereby minimise bias error.

column13: Bias error is reduced in a vibrating structure sensor having primary and secondary pick-off means (2, 3) separated by a fixed angular amount (45 DEG ) with respect to the vibrating structure by summing a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal (10) into the secondary pick-off means output signal (15) or subtracting a proportion of the primary pick-off means output signal (10) from the secondary pick-off means output signal (15) effectively to reduce or increase the angular separation of the secondary pick-off means (3) from the primary drive means (1) by an amount sufficient to set the rate output signal from the vibrating structure to zero and thereby minimise bias error.

column12: AN ANGULAR RATE SENSOR
column13: An angular rate sensor or gyro includes a ring-like resonator (1) mounted by support beams (2) extending from the inner periphery of the ring (1) to a boss (4) on a base (3). The support beams (2) are flexible and allow the resonator (1) to vibrate in response to an electrostatic drive (6, 8) in a substantially undamped oscillation mode to permit the resonator to move relative to the support in response to turning rate. The support beams (2) and resonator (1) are made from crystalline silicon. Electrostatic sensors (7, 9) are provided for sensing movement of the resonator (1). The drive (6, 8) and sensors (7, 9) have plate-like elements made from crystalline silicon having surfaces located substantially normal to the plane of the resonator (1) at a spacing from the adjacent outer periphery of the resonator (1). The ratio of the thickness of the resonator (1) at the outer periphery (1b) to the width of the spacing (11) between the periphery (1b) and the element surfaces (10) is in the range of from 10:1 to 40:1.

column12: Calças ìntimas descartáveis incluindo núcleo absorvente enviesado
column13: <B>CALçAS ìNTIMAS DESCARTáVEIS INCLUINDO NúCLEO ABSORVENTE ENVIESADO<D> Calça íntima descartável tridimensional que tem um núcleo absorvente inclinado para frente em um fator de não mais do que 0,1555. O núcleo absorvente está disposto dentro das seções frontal, central e posterior da calça íntima descartável de tal modo que o comprimento do núcleo absorvente na seção posterior da calça íntima descartável dividido pelo comprimento do núcleo absorvente na seção frontal e na seção central da calça íntima descartável é menor do que 0,155, e o comprimento do núcleo absorvente, na seção frontal da calça íntima descartável, é maior do que o comprimento do núcleo absorvente na seção posterior da calça íntima descartável. A calça íntima descartável pode incluir aberturas elastificadas de perna e de cintura, resultando na calça íntima sendo esticável em torno das regiões dos quadris e estómago de um usuário.

column12: DISPOSABLE UNDERPANTS INCLUDING SKEWED ABSORBENT CORE
column13: A three dimensional disposable underpant having an absorbent core has been skewed forward by a factor of no more than 0.155. The absorbent core is disposed within the front, central, and back sections of the disposable underpant such that the length of the absorbent core in the back section of the disposable underpant divided by the length of the absorbent core in the front and central sections of the disposable underpant is less than 0.155 and the length of the absorbent core in the front section of the disposable underpant is greater than the length of the absorbent core in the back section of the disposable underpant. The disposable underpant may include elasticized leg and waist openings, resulting in the underpant being stretchable about the hip and stomach regions of a user.

column12: Round baler having trash discharge mechanism
column13: An apparatus for forming large round bales of crop material includes a frame (10) having a pair of side walls (12, 14) and ground engaging wheels (18) mounted on the frame for supporting the apparatus for movement across the ground. A plurality of rollers (24, 26, 28, 30, 32, 34, 36, 38) are mounted for rotatable movement relative to the frame (10) and extend between the side walls (12, 14), and a plurality of endless bale forming belts (46) are trained about the rollers to define a bale forming chamber (16) in which large round bales of crop materials are formed. At least one additional chamber (48) is also defined by the bale forming belts (46) adjacent the bale forming chamber (16). A clean-out assembly (54) is provided for cleaning crop material from the additional chamber. The clean-out assembly (54) includes an opening (64) in one of the side walls (12) of the baler and a clean-out belt mounted on a pair of pulleys (56, 58) for sweeping crop material in a direction toward the opening in the side wall so that material within the additional chamber (48) is swept from the apparatus through the opening (64).

column12: Absorbent article having a multiplayer blended core and a method of forming
column13: An absorbent article, such as a thin incontinence pad or pantyliner, is disclosed which has an absorbent core formed from multiple layers of blended material for providing protection against involuntary urine loss. A method of forming the absorbent article is also disclosed. The absorbent article includes a liquid permeable bodyside liner, a liquid-impermeable baffle, and first and second absorbents positioned between the liner and the baffle. The first absorbent is a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent and has a predetermined basis weight. The second absorbent is also a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent. The second absorbent is positioned below the first absorbent and has a basis weight that is at least equal to the basis weight of the first absorbent.
column15: FELL DAVID ARTHUR;;GEORGER WILLIAM ANTHONY;;SUPRISE JODY DOROTHY

column12: UN CONJUNTO ABSORBENTE, UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE QUE RESISTE LAS ARRUGAS PERMANENTES Y METODO PARA UTILIZAR DICHO ARTICULO ABSORBENTE
column13: Un conjunto absorbente que incluye un componente de envase y un artículo absorbente que se coloca de manera retirable en el componente de envase. El artículo absorbente incluye por lo menos partes primera y segunda, cada una de las cuales define una superficie de frente al cuerpo. El artículo absorbente se mueve de manera independiente desde una condición plegada, en la cual las superficies de frente al cuerpo de las partes primera y segunda se encuentran de frente entre sí, en una relación esencialmente paralela, bajo una presión aplicada a las partes primera y segunda, hasta una condición desplegada, en la cual no se aplica ninguna presión a las partes primera y segunda. Las superficies de frente al cuerpo de las partes primera y segunda forman por lo menos un ángulo mayor que 90° en la condición desplegada cuando el artículo absorbente se coloca en la condición plegada bajo 2.800 libras por pulgada cuadrada de presión aplicada durante alrededor de 5 segundos, y luego se libera a la condición desplegada durante alrededor de 20 segundos. En otro aspecto adicional, el artículo absorbente además incluye una tercera parte que posee una superficie de frente al cuerpo. Las superficies de frente al cuerpo de las partes primera y tercera se pliegan, para encontrarse de frente a la superficie de frente al cuerpo de dicha segunda parte, lo cual produce un artículo plegado en tres partes.

column12: Artigo absorvente com um núcleo de múltiplas camadas combinadas e um método de formação
column13: "ARTIGO ABSORVENTE COM UM NúCLEO DE MúLTIPLAS CAMADAS COMBINADAS E UM MéTODO DE FORMAçãO". é apresentado um artigo absorvente, tal como um chumaço para incontinência ou forro de calça fino, que tem um núcleo absorvente formado a partir de múltiplas camadas de material combinadas para propiciar proteção contra perda involuntária de fluidos corporais. é também ensinado um método de formação do artigo absorvente. O artigo absorvente inclui um forro permeável a líquido virado para o corpo, um difusor impermeável a líquido e primeiro e segundo absorventes posicionados entre o forro e o difusor. o primeiro absorvente é um material estabilizado que contém um superabsorvente e tem um peso base predeterminado. O segundo absorvente é também um material estabilizado que contém um superabsorvente. o segundo absorvente está posicionado debaixo do primeiro absorvente e tem um peso base que é pelo menos igual ao peso base do primeiro absorvente.
column15: FELL DAVID ARTHUR;;GEORGER WILLIAM ANTHONY;;SUPRISE JODY DOROTHY

column12: Fold line resistant absorbent articles
column13: An absorbent system includes a packaging component and an absorbent article that is removably disposed in the packaging component. The absorbent article includes at least first and second portions, each defining a body side surface. The absorbent article is independently movable from a folded condition, wherein the body side surfaces of the first and second portions face each other in a substantially parallel relationship under an applied pressure applied to the first and second portions, to an unfolded condition, wherein no pressure is applied to the first and second portions. The body-side surfaces of the first and second portions form at least one angle greater than 90° in the unfolded condition when the absorbent article is positioned in the folded condition under 2800 psi of applied pressure for about 5 seconds and then is released to the unfolded condition for about 20 seconds. In yet another aspect, the absorbent article further includes a third portion having a body-side surface. The body-side surfaces of the first and third portions are folded to face the body-side surface of said second portion, producing a tri-folded article.
column14: FELL DAVID A.;;DELLERMAN PAIGE A.;;BATH JAMES R.

column13: An absorbent article, such as a thin incontinence pad or pantyliner, is disclosed which has an absorbent core formed from multiple layers of blended material for providing protection against involuntary urine loss. A method of forming the absorbent article is also disclosed. The absorbent article includes a liquid permeable bodyside liner, a liquid-impermeable baffle, and first and second absorbents positioned between the liner and the baffle. The first absorbent is a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent and has a predetermined basis weight. The second absorbent is also a stabilized material containing a superabsorbent. The second absorbent is positioned below the first absorbent and has a basis weight that is at least equal to the basis weight of the first absorbent.

column12: THREE DIMENSIONALLY PATTERNED STABILIZED ABSORBENT MATERIAL AND METHOD FOR PRODUCING SAME
column13: An absorbent core for use in an absorbent article such as a diaper, training pant, feminine hygiene product, or an incontinence product includes a three dimensionally patterned stabilized first absorbent layer and a second absorbent layer adjacent the first layer. An upper surface of the first three dimensionally patterned stabilized absorbent layer has a three-dimensional topography relative to the longitudinal and lateral axes and defines a plurality of peaks and valleys of the upper surface relative to the z-direction. A lower surface of the first three dimensionally patterned stabilized absorbent layer has a three-dimensional topography relative to the longitudinal and lateral axes and defines a plurality of the peaks and valleys of the lower surface relative to the z-direction.

column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE QUE TIENE UN NUCLEO MEZCLADO DE CAPAS MULTIPLES Y UN METODO DE FORMACION
column13: Se describe un articulo absorbente tal como una almohadilla para incontinencia delgada o forro para bragas el cual tiene un nucleo absorbente formado de capas multiples de material mezclado para proporcionar una proteccion en contra de la perdida involuntaria de orina. Tambien se describe un metodo para formar el articulo absorbente. El articulo absorbente incluye un forro de lado al cuerpo permeable al liquido, un separador impermeable al liquido, y los absorbentes primero y segundo colocados entre el forro y el separador. El primer absorbente es un material estabilizado que contiene un superabsorbente y tiene un peso base predeterminado. El segundo absorbente tambien es un material estabilizado que contiene un superabsorbente. El segundo absorbente esta colocado debajo del primer absorbente y tiene un peso base que es por lo menos igual al peso base del primer absorbente.

column12: RECOVERY METHOD FOR A PORTABLE DATA PROCESSING APPARATUS
column13: A system for the recovery of the software configuration of a mobile digital assistant (1). The profile of the digital assistant is stored on a database (9) of a management server (7). The apparatus carries recovery software. In the event of a failure, the digital assistant communicates with a configuration workstation (5), which identifies the digital assistant and supplies its identity to the management server (7). In accordance with the stored profile, the appropriate software or configuration settings are supplied to the digital assistant to effect recovery. If the digital assistant's profile cannot be identified, a management information server is used to determine the correct configuration for the type of digital assistant concerned.

column12: Non-invasive pneumothorax detection method and apparatus
column13: Provided is a micropower impulse radar (MIR) pneumothorax detector. The detector includes a processor and a handheld MIR scanner. The handheld MIR scanner includes a device housing, an antenna located within the device housing, circuitry that generates MIR signals, and circuitry that processes received echoes of the MIR signals and provides the processed received echoes to the processor. The processor automatically determines whether a pneumothorax is present based on the processed received echoes of the MIR signals.

column12: VIBRATING STRUCTURE GYROSCOPE WITH A VIBRATION DAMPER ASSEMBLY
column13: A vibration damper assembly for a ring resonator of a vibrating structure gyroscope has a female portion attachable to a body of the gyroscope so as to have limited resiliency with respect to the body in a direction substantially perpendicular to the body. A male portion is fixedly attachable at one end to a resonator of the gyroscope, projectable into the female portion and fixedly attachable at its other end in and to the female portion. The assembly permits damping of vibratory movement of the resonator in a direction substantially perpendicular thereto whilst retaining stiffness and freedom to vibrate for the resonator in the plane thereof.
column15: FELL CHRISTOPHER PAUL;;HOPKIN IAN DAVID;;MASON TIMOTHY ROBERT;;TOWNSEND KEVIN

column12: Vibrating structure gyroscope
column13: A vibrating structure gyroscope has a vibratory resonator having a substantially ring or hoop-like shape structure, an electromagnetic drive for causing the resonator to vibrate, a support structure including a plurality of flexible support beams for supporting the resonator whilst allowing it to vibrate and an electromagnetic sensor for sensing movement of the resonator. The support beams and resonator are made from silicon and the electromagnetic drive and sensor include metal tracks which extend externally along each support beam onto and along respective segments of an outer substantially planar surface of the ring-like resonator. The resonator is substantially planar and means is produced a magnetic field substantially perpendicular to the plane of the resonator.

column12: VIBRATION STRUCTURE GYROSCOPE
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an improved vibration structure gyroscope which does not sense unnecessary vibration, an solve problems in manufacture. SOLUTION: A vibration structure gyroscope comprises a substantially flat vibration resonator 1 comprising a substantially ring-like or annular structure body provided with an inside circumference part 2 extending around a common axis line and an outside circumference part 3, an electro-magnetic driving means which causes vibration with the resonator 1, a supporting means comprising plural flexible supporting beams 5 which support the resonator 1, and an electro- magnetic sensing means which senses action of the resonator 1. The supporting beam 5 is allowed to vibrate the resonator 1 substantially in non-attenuation vibration mode in response to the electro-magnetic driving means, so that the resonator 1 may act to the supporting means according to rotation speed. With the supporting beam 5 and the resonator 1 made of silicon, the electro-magnetic driving means and electro-magnetic sensing means is provided with a metal track on the supporting beam 5 and' the resonator 1 of ring-like annular structure, while a means for generating such magnetic field substantially vertical to the plane of vibration resonator 1 provided.
column15: HOPKIN IAN DAVID;;FELL CHRISTOPHER PAUL;;TOWNSEND KEVIN;;MASON TIMOTHY ROBERT

column12: A vibrating structure gyroscope

The support beams (5) and resonator (1) are made from silicon and the electromagnetic drive and sensing means are provided by metal tracks (7, 8) which extend externally along each support beam (5) onto and along respective segments of an outer substantially planar surface (1a) the ring-like resonator (1). The support beams (5) and resonator (1) are made from silicon and the electromagnetic drive and sensing means are provided by metal tracks (7, 8) which extend externally along each support beam (5) onto and along respective segments of an outer substantially planar surface (1a) the ring-like resonator (1). The resonator (1) is substantially planar and means (13, 14, 14a) are provided to produce a magnetic field substantially perpendicular to the plane of the resonator (1).
column15: HOPKIN IAN DAVID;;FELL CHRISTOPHER PAUL;;TOWNSEND KEVIN;;MASON TIMOTHY ROBERT

column12: A VIBRATION DAMPER ASSEMBLY FOR A VIBRATING STRUCTURE GYROSCOPE RESONATOR
column13: A vibration damper assembly (7) for a ring resonator (1) of a vibrating structure gyroscope has a female portion attachable to a body (8) of the gyroscope so as to have limited resiliency with respect to the body (8) in a direction substantially perpendicular to the body. A male portion is fixedly attachable at one end to a resonator (1) of the gyroscope, projectable into the female portion and fixedly attachable at its other end in and to the female portion. The assembly permits damping of vibratory movement of the resonator (1) in a direction substantially perpendicular thereto whilst retaining stiffness and freedom to vibrate for the resonator (1) in the plane thereof.

column12: ABSORBENT ARTICLE HAVING ELASTICIZED BUMPERS AND METHOD OF MANUFACTURE.
column13: An absorbent article includes a moisture barrier, a bodyside liner bonded to the moisture barrier, and an absorbent structure disposed between the bodyside liner and moisture barrier. Elasticized bumpers which function as three-dimensional physical barriers to liquid movement are disposed in the margins of the article. The elasticized bumpers include an internal barrier structure and an elasticized cover disposed over the internal barrier structure and bonded to one of the margins. In particular embodiments, the elasticized cover is formed of a hydrophobic material, is unadhered to the internal barrier structure, and/or is comprised of elastic strands of variable degrees of power. A method of making the absorbent article includes the steps of providing a continuous carrier web having opposite side edges and disposing a continuous absorbent web on the continuous carrier web between the side edges. Continuous strands of an internal barrier material are disposed on the continuous carrier web with one of the strands being located between the absorbent web and each of the side edges. The continuous carrier web, absorbent web and strands of internal barrier material forming a continuous in-process composite structure which is transversely cut to form a plurality of individual, in-process composite structures. Each individual, in-process composite structure includes an absorbent structure and a pair of internal barrier structures disposed on a carrier sheet. The method also includes disposing the individual, in-process composite structures on a continuous moisture barrier web, and providing a pair of continuous covers. The continuous covers are elasticized over at least part of their length and are positioning over the internal barrier structures. The continuous covers are bonded to the moisture barrier and the moisture barrier web and the covers are cut between the individual, in-process composite structures.
column15: FELL DAVID ARTHUR;;KECK PHILLIP EUGENE;;ARTEMAN DAVID JEROME;;LEMAHIEU LYNN KIRKPATRICK;;JOHNSTON JERRY ALAN

column12: BODY ADHERING ABSORBENT ARTICLE
column13: A feminine care absorbent article has an absorbent structure configured for disposition adjacent a female wearer's vaginal region to absorb bodily fluids discharged by the wearer, and a shell for supporting the absorbent structure at the vaginal region. The shell has a body- facing surface and a garment-facing surface. The body-facing surface has an adhesive thereon for adhering the shell directly to the wearer. The shell has a longitudinal axis, a transverse axis, an anterior region, a posterior region, and a central region extending longitudinally between and interconnecting the anterior and posterior regions. The anterior region of the shell includes a longitudinal edge having a longitudinal extent from the transverse axis. The longitudinal extent increases as the longitudinal edge extends transversely outward from the longitudinal axis of the shell.

column13: Un artículo absorbente que comprende: una barrera a la humedad que tiene bordes de extremo longitudinales y bordes laterales longitudinales que se extienden entre los bordes de extremo; un forro del lado del cuerpo unido a la barrera de humedad; una estructura absorbente dispuesta entre el forro del lado del cuerpo y la barrera a la humedad formando márgenes opuestos que se extienden más allá de la estructura absorbente, y un paratopes o amortiguador elastificado dispuesto en cada uno de los márgenes, cada uno de los paratopes elastificados que comprende: una estructura de barrera interna formada de un material resiliente unido a uno de los márgenes; y una cubierta elastificada dispuesta sobre la estructura de barrera interna y pegada a uno de los márgenes, la cubierta elastificada, formada de un material hidrofóbico. 2El artículo absorbente de la reivindicación 4, donde por lo menos una de las bandas elásticas tiene mayor potencia elástica que por lo menos otra de las bandas elásticas.

column12: BODY ADHERING ABSORBENT ARTICLE
column13: A feminine care absorbent article has an absorbent structure configured for disposition adjacent a female wearer's vaginal region to absorb bodily fluids discharged by the wearer, and a shell for supporting the absorbent structure at the vaginal region. The shell has a body-facing surface and a garment-facing surface. The body-facing surface has an adhesive thereon for adhering the shell directly to the wearer. The shell has a longitudinal axis, a transverse axis, an anterior region, a posterior region, and a central region extending longitudinally between and interconnecting the anterior and posterior regions. The anterior region of the shell includes a longitudinal edge having a longitudinal extent from the transverse axis. The longitudinal extent increases as the longitudinal edge extends transversely outward from the longitudinal axis of the shell.

column12: UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE PARA EL CUIDADO FEMENINO
column13: Un artículo absorbente para el cuidado femenino tiene una estructura absorbente configurada para ser ubicada adyacente a la region vaginal de una usuaria femenina para absorber fluidos corporales descargados por el usuario, y una cubierta para soportar la estructura absorbente en la region vaginal. la cubierta tiene una superficie enfrentando al cuerpo y una superficie enfrentando la prenda. La superficie enfrentando al cuerpo tiene un adhesivo en la misma para adherir la cubierta directamente al usuario. La cubierta tiene un eje longitudinal, un eje transversal, una region anterior, una region posterior, una region central extendiéndose longitudinalmente entre e interconectando las regiones anteriores y posteriores. La region anterior de la cubierta incluye una orilla longitudinal con una extension longitudinal desde el eje transversal. La extension longitudinal se incrementa a medida que la orilla longitudinal se extiende transversalmente hacia afuera desde el eje longitudinal de la cubierta.

column13: 여성 위생 흡수 용품은 착용자가 배출한 체액을 흡수하기 위해 여성 착용자의 질 영역에 인접 배치되도록 구성된 흡수 구조체, 및 질 영역에 흡수 구조체를 지지하기 위한 쉘을 가진다. 쉘은 신체 대향면 및 가먼트 대향면을 가진다. 신체 대향면은 착용자에게 직접 쉘을 접착하기 위한 접착제를 위에 가진다. 쉘은 종축, 횡축, 전방 영역, 후방 영역, 및 전방 영역과 후방 영역 사이에서 종방향으로 연장되고 전방 영역과 후방 영역을 상호 연결하는 중앙 영역을 가진다. 쉘의 전방 영역은 횡축으로부터 종방향 한계를 가지는 종방향 연부를 포함한다. 종방향 한계는 종방향 연부가 쉘의 종축으로부터 횡방향으로 바깥쪽으로 연장됨에 따라 증가한다.

column12: PICKUP AND DELIVERY OF DATA FILES
column13: A data file is regarded as a digital package. A convenient interface is provided for scheduling pickup and delivery of the data file via one or more satellite communication links. The data file may represent various types of information, such as text, images, audio or video. A centralized system receives the scheduling order and arranges for the data file to be automatically picked up from one or more locations and delivered to one or more destinations. The delivery service may include buffering the data file for a predetermined time period to comply with the scheduled delivery time. The centralized system provides a scheduling confirmation notice for the scheduled pickup and delivery, and also provides notice that the data file was actually delivered. The centralized system maintains an activity log useful for status inquiry and billing. In short, the centralized system functions as a 'dispatcher' for bits, within an infrastructure for receiving, tracking, deliivering and billing based on bits.

column12: Absorbent composite with a resilient coform layer
column13: An absorbent composite disposed in an absorbent article between a topsheet and a backsheet is presented, the absorbent composite including a first intake layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, and a retention layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, wherein one of the first intake layer and the retention layer includes a resilient coform material. When the first intake layer includes a resilient coform material, the retention layer includes one of a high-density, hydrogen-bonded, fluff/superabsorbent polymer material, a spunlace material, a superabsorbent polymer/adhesive composite material, and a foam material. The absorbent composite can further include a distribution layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, the distribution layer including one of a meltblown microfiber material, a spunlace material, and a foam material.

column12: UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE PARA LA INCONTINENCIA DEL ADULTO, UN PAQUETE QUE COMPRENDE DICHO ARTICULO Y UN ARREGLO DE DICHO ARTICULO
column13: Se revelan disenos de productos absorbentes descartables para la incontinencia del adulto hechos a la medida de las distintas características anatomicas entre el cuerpo de un hombre y de una mujer. Los disenos tienen en cuenta las distintas manerasen que los hombres y las mujeres envejecen y típicamente distribuyen su peso corporal. Por ejemplo, un artículo descartable para la incontinencia del adulto adaptado para el uso por parte de mujeres puede emplear distintas formas de abertura depierna, ubicacion del absorbente, características ornamentales u otras características, comparado con un correspondiente artículo adaptado para el uso por parte de hombres. Se revelan asimismo maneras de envasar y comercializar dichos productos demanera de dar a conocer los arreglos revelados de artículos descartables para la incontinencia del adulto, específicos para el género, así como de artículos descartables para la incontinencia del adulto, específicos para el género, individuales.

column12: Pickup and delivery of data files
column13: A data file is regarded as a digital package. A conventional interface is provided for scheduling pickup and delivery of the data file via one or more satellite communications links. The data file may represent various types of information, such as text, images, audio or video. A centralized system receives the scheduling order and arranges for the data file to be automatically picked up from one or more locations and delivered to one or more destinations. The delivery service may include buffering the data file for a predetermined time period to comply with the scheduled delivery time. The centralized system provides a scheduling confirmation notice for the scheduled pickup and delivery, and also provides notice that the data file was actually delivered. The centralized system maintains an activity log useful for status inquiry and billing. In short, the centralized system functions as a dispatcher for bits, within an infrastructure for receiving, tracking, delivery and billing based on bits.

column12: Absorbent Composite With A Resilient Coform Layer
column13: An absorbent composite disposed in an absorbent article between a topsheet and a backsheet is presented, the absorbent composite including a first intake layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, and a retention layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, wherein one of the first intake layer and the retention layer includes a resilient coform material. When the first intake layer includes a resilient coform material, the retention layer includes one of a high-density, hydrogen-bonded, fluff/superabsorbent polymer material, a spunlace material, a superabsorbent polymer/adhesive composite material, and a foam material. The absorbent composite can further include a distribution layer disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet, the distribution layer including one of a meltblown microfiber material, a spunlace material, and a foam material.

column12: UN COMPUESTO ABSORBENTE DISPUESTO EN UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE ENTRE UNA HOJA SUPERIOR Y UNA HOJA INFERIOR
column13: Se presenta un compuesto absorbente dispuesto en un artículo absorbente entre una hoja superior y una hoja inferior, el compuesto absorbente incluye una primera capa de entrada dispuesta entre la hoja superior y la hoja inferior, y una capa de retención dispuesta entre la hoja superior y la hoja inferior, en donde una de la primera capa de entrada y la capa de retención incluye un material conformado resiliente. Cuando la primera capa de retención incluye un material conformado resiliente, la capa de retención incluye uno de un material de polímero de borra/superabsorbente unido por hidrógeno de alta densidad, un material hilado y entrelazado, un material compuesto de polímero/adhesivo superabsorbente, y un material de espuma. El compuesto absorbente puede además incluir una capa de distribución dispuesta entre la hoja superior y la hoja inferior, la capa de distribución incluye uno de un material de microfibra soplada con fusión, un material hilado y entrelazado y un material de espuma.

column12: ABSORBENT STRUCTURE WITH AGGREGATE CLUSTERS
column13: An absorbent structure has a macro absorbent structure with a plurality of aggregate clusters intermixed therein. The aggregate clusters have a periphery, an interior, and thermoplastic binder fibers. The thermoplastic binder fibers have thermoplastic binder fiber ends. The thermoplastic binder fiber ends are located at the periphery of the aggregate clusters. The interior of the aggregate clusters are substantially free of thermoplastic binder fiber ends. The macro absorbent structure and the aggregate clusters may also include thermoplastic binder fibers, staple fibers, superabsorbent particles and the like. A method of making absorbent structures includes a first absorbent structure, dividing the first absorbent structure to create aggregate clusters, providing a stream of the aggregate clusters, providing polymeric fibers, merging the aggregate cluster stream and polymeric fiber stream into a single product stream, and making a second absorbent structure. The method may further include staple fibers, superabsorbent particles, and the like.

column13: Disposable adult-incontinence product designs tailored to the differing anatomical features of a man's body and a woman's body are disclosed. The designs take into account differing ways in which men and women age and typically distribute weight. Also disclosed are ways of packaging and marketing said products to help create public awareness of the disclosed arrays of gender-specific, disposable, adult-incontinence articles, as well as individual, gender-specific, disposable, adult-incontinence articles.

column12: An absorbent article with an improved, wet-formed absorbent
column13: The present invention provides an absorbent articled (10) having a longitudinal direction (26), and a lateral, cross direction (24). The article includes a liquid permeable top sheet layer (28), a substantially liquid impermeable backsheet layer (30), and an absorbent structure (32) having a primary retention portion (48) sandwiched between the top sheet and backsheet layers. The retention portion (48) includes a wet formed mixture of fibers and superabsorbent material. The retention portion has a selected edge-wise compression value, such an edge-wise compression value of not more than a maximum of about 9 g/gsm, and a modified circular bend value, such as a modified circular bend value of at least minimum of about 0.3 g/gsm. In particular aspects, the retention portion (48) can include cellulosic fibers.

column12: GENDER-SPECIFIC, DISPOSABLE, ADULT-INCONTINENCE ARTICLES
column13: Disposable adult-incontinence product designs tailored to the differing anatomical features of a man's body and a woman's body are disclosed. The designs take into account differing ways in which men and women age and typically distribute weight. For example, a disposable, adult-incontinence article adapted to be worn by women may employ different leg-opening shapes, absorbent placement, ornamental features, and/or other characteristics compared to a corresponding article adapted to be worn by men. Also disclosed are ways of packaging and marketing said products to help create public awareness of the disclosed arrays of gender-specific, disposable, adult-incontinence articles, as well as individual, gender-specific, disposable, adult-incontinence articles.

column12: Absorbent structure with aggregate clusters
column13: An absorbent structure has a macro absorbent structure with a plurality of aggregate clusters intermixed therein. The aggregate clusters have a periphery, an interior, and thermoplastic binder fibers. The thermoplastic binder fibers have thermoplastic binder fiber ends. The thermoplastic binder fiber ends are located at the periphery of the aggregate clusters. The interior of the aggregate clusters are substantially free of thermoplastic binder fiber ends. The macro absorbent structure and the aggregate clusters may also include thermoplastic binder fibers, staple fibers, superabsorbent particles and the like. A method of making absorbent structures includes a first absorbent structure, dividing the first absorbent structure to create aggregate clusters, providing a stream of the aggregate clusters, providing polymeric fibers, merging the aggregate cluster stream and polymeric fiber stream into a single product stream, and making a second absorbent structure. The method may further include staple fibers, superabsorbent particles, and the like.

column12: Absorbent garment with an extensible backsheet and the method for absorbing bodily exudates with the same
column13: An absorbent garment includes an extensible backsheet having opposite side regions, a liquid permeable topsheet having opposite side portions, and a retention portion having opposite side edges and an outer surface defining an area. The retention portion is disposed between the topsheet and the backsheet with the outer surface facing the backsheet and with the opposite side portions of the backsheet and the topsheet extending beyond the side edges of the retention portion. The opposite side portions of the topsheet are attached to the opposite side portions of the backsheet on opposite sides of the retention portion. Less than 30% of the area of the outer surface of the retention portion is attached to the backsheet. In one preferred embodiment, the retention portion is freefloating between the backsheet and topsheet. In one preferred embodiment, the topsheet is extensible. In another preferred embodiment, less than 30% of an inner surface of the retention portion is attached to the topsheet. In yet another preferred embodiment, the retention portion includes at least one fold. Preferably, the backsheet, and more preferably the backsheet and topsheet, have ear portions that are secured to form leg openings. In this way, the backsheet and topsheet define the shape or plan surface area of the garment, without the need for additional body panels. A method for absorbing bodily exudates with an absorbent garment is also provided.

column12: REFASTENABLE ABSORBENT ARTICLE
column13: An absorbent article is disclosed having a refastenable mechanism. The absorbent article has a front portion, a back portion and a crotch portion. The crotch portion connects the front portion to the back portion. The front portion has a first end, a second end, a first side edge and a second side edge. First and second lateral sections are releasably attached to the front portion and each of the first and second lateral sections has an outer edge. The back portion has first and second side edges and first and second ends. The back portion is divided into a first section and a second section. The first section has a length L2 measured perpendicularly from the first end of the back portion to a line drawn parallel thereto. The second section has a length L3 measured perpendicularly from the second end of the back portion to the line drawn parallel to the first end whereby a ratio L2/L3 is established which ranges from between about 0.1 to about 2. The absorbent article further includes an absorbent secured to at least one of the front, back or crotch portions. Each of the outer edges of the first and second lateral sections are secured to one of the first and second side edges of the back portion to form a pant-like article having a waist opening and a pair of leg openings.

column12: método para formar uma trama absorvente com propriedades de controle de odor
column13: <b>artigos absorventes com controle de odor aperfeiçoado<d> é provida uma técnica para incorporar partículas de agente de controle de odor em um artigo absorvente. mais especificamente, as partículas de controle de odor sào distribuídas "homogeneamente" (por exemplo, de uma maneira substancialmente uniforme) dentro de uma matriz de fibra formada a ar de um núcleo absorvente de um artigo absorvente. um núcleo absorvente contendo tais partículas de controle de odor homogeneamente distribuídas pode possuir uma área de superfície maior para contatar os compostos fétidos, desse modo aumentando a probabilidade de redução de odor.

column12: Absorbent articles with improved odor control
column13: A technique for incorporating odor control agent particles into an absorbent article is provided. More specifically, the odor control particles are “homogenously” distributed (e.g., in a substantially uniform manner) within an airformed fiber matrix of an absorbent core of an absorbent article. column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE CON MECANISMO REAJUSTABLE
column13: EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE DE LA PRESENTE INVENCION COMPRENDE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR, UNA PORCION CORPORAL FRONTAL, UNA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR Y UNA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL. LA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL ES INTERMEDIA Y SE INTERCONECTA CON LA PORCION CORPORAL FRONTAL Y LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR. EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE INCLUYE ADEMAS UNA UNIDAD ABSORBENTE TIPICAMENTE ASOCIADA CON LA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL QUE TIENE UNA LAMINA POSTERIOR IMPERMEABLE AL LIQUIDO, UNA LAMINA SUPERIOR PERMEABLE AL LIQUIDO Y UN NUCLEO ABSORBENTE QUE ESTA COLOCADO ENTRE LA LAMINA POSTERIOR Y LA LAMINA SUPERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR INCLUYE UNA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA COMPRENDE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN PAR DE BORDES LATERALES OPUESTOS Y UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA TIENE MIEMBROS ELASTICOS. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR INCLUYE TAMBIEN UNA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA INCLUYE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN PAR DE BORDES LATERALES OPUESTOS Y UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA PUEDE TAMBIEN INCLUIR MIEMBROS ELASTICOS DE AJUSTE POSTERIOR, TIPICAMENTE COLOCADOS ADYACENTES POR LO MENOS A UNA PARTE DE LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA. LA PORCION CORPORAL FRONTAL DEL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE INCLUYE ADEMAS UNA REGION CENTRAL Y UN PAR DE REGIONES LATERALES. CADA REGION LATERAL INCLUYE UN PAR DE BORDES LATERALES OPUESTOS Y MIEMBROS ELASTICOS. CADA UNA DE LAS REGIONES LATERALES ESTA UNIDA A UNO DE LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA A LO LARGO DE LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LAS REGIONES LATERALES. CADA UNA DE LAS REGIONES LATERALES ESTA ADHERIDA O UNIDA DE FORMA QUE SE PUEDA SOLTAR A UNO DE LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LA OTRA REGION LATERAL A LO LARGO DEL OTRO EXTREMO LATERAL DE LAS REGIONES LATERALES. LAS REGIONES LATERALES ESTAN SUPERPUESTAS A LA REGION CENTRAL. LAS REGIONES LATERALES PUEDEN MANTENER ESTA RELACION DE SUPERPOSICION O CONTACTO MEDIANTE EL ENGANCHE DEL PRIMER Y SEGUNDO ELEMENTOS DE AFIANZAMIENTO.
column15: FREIBURGER SARAH JANE MARIE;;BRUEMMER-PRESTLEY MARY ANNE;;BORDAIN NEFETARI EDRIS;;SCHMOKER SUZANNE MARIE;;FELL DAVID ARTHUR

column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE CON MECANISMO REAJUSTABLE
column13: SE EXPONE UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE DESECHABLE QUE TIENE UNA PORCIÓN FRONTAL, UNA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR Y UNA PORCIÓN DE LA ENTREPIERNA. LA PORCIÓN DE LA ENTREPIERNA UNE LA PORCIÓN FRONTAL Y LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR. LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR TIENE UN PRIMER EXTREMO Y UN SEGUNDO EXTREMO. LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR ESTÁ DIVIDIDA EN UNA PRIMERA SECCIÓN Y UNA SEGUNDA SECCIÓN. LA PRIMERA SECCIÓN PUEDE EXTENDERSE EN DIRECCIÓN TRANSVERSAL Y TIENE UNA LONGITUD L2 MEDIDA PERPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL PRIMER EXTREMO DE LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR A UNA LÍNEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL MISMO. LA SEGUNDA SECCIÓN TIENE UNA LONGITUD L3 MEDIDA PERPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO DE LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR A LA LÍNEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO. LA SEGUNDA SECCIÓN TIENE UN PRIMER BORDE LATERAL, UN SEGUNDO BORDE LATERAL, UNA PRIMERA ARREA A1 Y UNA SEGUNDA ARREA A2. LA PRIMERA ARREA A1 REPRESENTA UN ARREA DELIMITADA POR EL PRIMER Y SEGUNDO BORDES LATERALES, EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO Y LA LÍNEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO. LA SEGUNDA ÁREA A2 REPRESENTA UN ÁREA DELIMITADA POR LA PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA LÍNEAS, EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO Y LA LÍNEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO. LA PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA LÍNEAS SON TRAZADAS PERPENDICULARMENTE AL SEGUNDO EXTREMO EN LOS PUNTOS EN QUE EL PRIMER Y SEGUNDO BORDES LATERALES INTERCEPTAN EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO. LA PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA LÍNEAS INTERCEPTAN LA LÍNEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO. LA SEGUNDA SECCIÓN TIENE UNA RELACIÓN A1/A2 QUE VARÍA ENTRE 1.3 Y 3.5 APROXIMADAMENTE. EL PRIMER Y SEGUNDO AFIANZADORES ESTÁN SUJETADOS A LA PORCIÓN POSTERIOR. UN ABSORBENTE ES SUJETADO POR LO MENOS A UNA DE LAS PORCIONES FRONTAL, POSTERIOR O DE LA ENTREPIERNA. TANTO EL PRIMERO COMO EL SEGUNDO AFIANZADOR ESTÁN SUJETOS DE MANERA QUE SE PUEDAN SOLTAR A LA PORCIÓN FRONTAL PARA FORMAR UN ARTÍCULO SIMILAR A UN PANTALÓN CON UNA ABERTURA EN LA CINTURA Y UN PAR DE PERNERAS.

column12: artigos absorventes com controle de odor aperfeiçoado
column13: <b>ARTIGOS ABSORVENTES COM CONTROLE DE ODOR APERFEIçOADO<d> é provida uma técnica para incorporar partículas de agente de controle de odor em um artigo absorvente. Mais especificamente, as partículas de controle de odor sào distribuídas "homogeneamente" (por exemplo, de uma maneira substancialmente uniforme) dentro de uma matriz de fibra formada a ar de um núcleo absorvente de um artigo absorvente. Um núcleo absorvente contendo tais partículas de controle de odor homogeneamente distribuídas pode possuir uma área de superfície maior para contatar os compostos fétidos, desse modo aumentando a probabilidade de redução de odor.

column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE TENIENDO UN MECANISMO RE-AJUSTABLE CASO 16103
column13: SE HA INVENTADO UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE QUE PRESENTA UN MECANISMO RE-AJUSTABLE. EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE TIENE UNA PORCION ANTERIOR, UNA POSTERIOR Y OTRA DE ENTEPIERNA. LA PORCION DE ENTREPIERNA CONECTA LA PORCION ANTERIOR CON LA POSTERIOR. LA PORCION ANTERIOR TIENE UN PRIMER EXTREMO, UN SEGUNDO EXTREMO, UNA ORILLA LATERAL PRIMERA Y UNA ORILLA LATERAL SEGUNDA. LAS SECCIONES LATERALES PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA ESTAN SUJETAS EN FORMA RE-AJUSTABLE A LA PORCION ANTERIOR Y CADA UNA DE LAS SECCIONES LATERALES PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA TIENE UNA ORILLA EXTERIOR. LA PORCION POSTERIOR TIENE ORILLAS LATERALES PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA, ASI COMO EXTREMOS PRIMERO Y SEGUNDO, LA PORCION POSTERIOR ESTA DIVIDIDA EN UNA PRIMERA SECCION Y UNA SEGUNDA SECCION. LA PRIMERA SECCION TIENE UNA LONGITUD L2 MEDIDA PERPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL PRIMER EXTREMO DE LA PORCION POSTERIOR HASTA A UNA LINEA TRAZADA PARALELA A ESTE. LA SEGUNDA SECCION TIENE UNA LONGITUD L3 MEDIDA PERPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO DE LA PORCION POSTERIOR HASTA LA LINEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO, CON LO QUE SE ESTABLECE UNA RELACION L2/L3 QUE VARIA EN UN RANGO DE APROXIMADAMENTE 0.1 A 2. EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE ADEMAS INCLUYE UN ABSORBENTE SUJETO A AL MENOS UNA DE LAS PORCIONES ANTERIOR, POSTERIOR O DE ENTREPIERNA. CADA UNA DE LAS ORILLAS EXTERIORES DE LAS SECCIONES LATERALES PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA SE ENCUENTRAN SUJETAS A UNA DE LAS ORILLAS LATERALES PRIMERA O SEGUNDA DE LA PORCION POSTERIOR PARA FORMAR UN ARTICULO SIMILAR A UNA PANTALETA, TENIENDO UNA ABERTURA DE CINTURA Y UN PAR DE ABERTURAS DE PIERNAS.

column12: Absorbent article having a refastenable mechanism
column13: A disposable absorbent article is disclosed having a front portion, a back portion and a crotch portion. The crotch portion joins the front portion to the back portion. The second section has a length L _{ 3 } measured perpendicularly from the second end of the back portion to the line drawn parallel to the first end. The second section has a first side edge, a second side edge, a first area A _{ 1 } and a second area A _{ 2 } . The first area A _{ 1 } represents an area bounded by the first and second side edges, the second end, and the line drawn parallel to the first end. The second area A _{ 2 } represents an area bounded by first and second lines, the second end, and the line drawn parallel to the first end. The first and second lines are drawn perpendicular to the second end at points where the first and second side edges intersect the second end. The first and second lines intersect the line drawn parallel to the first end. The second section has a ratio A _{ 1 } /A _{ 2 } which ranges from between about 1.3 to about 3.5. First and second fasteners are secured to the back portion. An absorbent is secured to at least one of the front, back or crotch portions. Each of the first and second fasteners are releasably attached to the front portion to form a pant-like article having a waist opening and a pair of leg openings.

column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE TENIENDO UN MECANISMO RE-AJUSTABLE CASO 16106
column13: SE HA INVENTADO UN ARTICULO ABSORBENTE CON UNA PORCION ANTERIOR, UNA PORCION POSTERIOR Y UNA PORCION DE ENTREPIERNA. LA PORCION DE ENTREPIERNA CONECTA LA PORCION ANTERIOR CON LA PORCION POSTERIOR. LA PORCION POSTERIOR TIENE UN EXTREMO PRIMERO UN EXTREMO SEGUNDO Y ORILLAS LATERALES PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA. LA PROCION POSTERIOR ESTA DIVIDIDA EN UNA SECCION PRIMERA Y UNA SECCION SEGUNDA. LA PRIMERA ES EXTENSIBLE EN AL MENOS UNA DIRECCION Y TIENE UNA LONGITUD L2 MEDIDA PREPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL PRIMER EXTREMO DE LA PORCION POSTERIOR HASTA UNA LINEA TRAZADA PARALELA A ESTE. LA SEGUDA SECCION TIENE UNA LONGITUD L3 MEDIDA PERPENDICULARMENTE DESDE EL SEGUNDO EXTREMO DE LA PORCION POSTERIOR HASTA LA LINEA TRAZADA PARALELA AL PRIMER EXTREMO. LA SEGUNDA SECCION TIENE UNA ORILLA LATERAL PRIMERA, UNA ORILLA LATERAL SEGUNDA, UN AREA PRIMERA A1 Y UN AREA SEGUNDA A2. LA SEGUNDA AREA A2 REPRESENTA UN AREA DELIMITADA POR LAS LINEAS PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA ESTAN TRAZADAS PERPENDICULARMENTE AL SEGUNDO EXTREMO EN PUNTOD DONDE LAS ORILLAS LATERALES PRIMNERA Y SEGUNDA INTERCEPTAN EL SEGUNDO EXTREM. LA SEGUNDA SECCION TIENE UNA RELACION A1/A2 QUE VARIA EN UN RANGO ENTRE APROXIMADAMENTE 1.3 A 3.5. LOS SUJETOS PRIMERO Y SEGUNDO ESTAN FIJADOS A LA PORCION PORSTERIOR. UN ARTICULO SE ENCUENTRA SUJETO A AL MENOS UNA DE LAS PORCIONES ANTERIORES, POSTERIOR O DE ENTREPIERNA. CADA UNO DE LOS SUJETADORES PRIMERO Y SEGUNDO ESTA FIJAO EN FORMA RE-AJUSTABLE A LA PORCION ANTERIOR PARA FORMAR UN ARTICULO SIMILIAR A UNA PATALTA QUE TIENE UNA ABERTURA DE CINTURA Y UN PAR DE ABERTURAS PARA LAS PIERNAS.

column12: ARTICULO ABSORBENTE CON AJUSTE AL CUERPO MEJORADO
column13: EL ARTICULO ABSORBENTE DE LA PRESENTE INVENCION COMPRENDE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR, UNA PORCION CORPORAL FRONTAL, UNA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR Y UNA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL. LA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL ES INTERMEDIA Y SE INTERCONECTA CON LA PORCION CORPORAL FRONTAL Y LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR. EL ARTICULO OBSORBENTE INCLUYE ADEMAS UNA UNIDAD ABSORBENTE ASOCIADA TIPICAMENTE CON LA PORCION CORPORAL CENTRAL QUE TIENE UNA LAMINA POSTERIOR IMPERMEABLE AL LIQUIDO, UNA LAMINA SUPERIOR PERMEABLE AL LIQUIDO, Y UN NUCLEO ABSORBENTE COLOCADO ENTRE LA LAMINA POSTERIOR Y LA LAMINA SUPERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR INCLUYE UNA PORCION POSTERIOR ALTA. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA COMPRENDE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN PAR DE BORDES LATERALES OPUESTOS Y UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR ALTA TIENE MIEMBROS ELASTICOS. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR TAMBIEN INCLUYE UNA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA COMPRENDE UN BORDE EXTREMO FRONTAL, UN PAR DE BORDES LATERALES OPUESTOS Y UN BORDE EXTREMO POSTERIOR. LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA INCLUYE ADEMAS MIEMBROS ELASTICOS DE AJUSTE POSTERIORES, TIPICAMENTE COLOCADOS DE MANERA ADYACENTE POR LO MENOS EN LOS BORDES LATERALES DE LA PORCION CORPORAL POSTERIOR BAJA.
